\n

Welcome to the official blog of the translators team for the WordPress open source project.

\n

This is where we discuss all things related to translating WordPress. Follow our progress for general updates, status reports, and debates.

\n

Wed love for you to help out.

\n
\n
\n

Translate WordPress

\n

You can help translating WordPress to your language at any time. Just log in to the translation platform with your WordPress.org account,and suggest translations. If you want to help in managing and validating translations, please make sure to get in touch with the existing language team and follow theglossaries & style guides if the team has them.

\n

Dont see your language?

\n

Request support for it by following this guide.

\n
\n
\n

Weekly Meetings

\n

We have two weekly meetings on Slack in #polyglots, on Wednesday 06:00 UTC and Wednesday 10:00 UTC. If you have any questions, bring them to the weekly chats!

\n

Posting here

\n

In order to post to this site, you will need to log in with your wordpress.org account. Your first post may take a while to show up, as it is moderated. Please follow our tag policy when posting.

      Below is a list of languages WordPress supports and their translation status of the core project.If you are interested in helping them translate WordPress or other related projects, please read the Translator Handbook or contact the translation editor(s) for your language using the Team link.

      \n

      If youd like to help an inactive team, please see the Inactive Translations page.

      \n\tReleases: 180 locales. 51 locales up to date. 8 locales behind by minor versions. 19 locales behind by one major version. 34 locales behind more than one major version. 59 locales have a site but never released. 9 locales dont have a site.\t

      \n\n\t

      \n\tTranslations: 180 locales. 18 locales at 100%. 47 locales have more than 95%. 8 locales have more than 90%. 35 locales have more than 50%. 64 locales have less than 50%. 110 locales have a language pack. 70 locales have no language pack. 8 locales dont have a WP project.\t
